  <source>Fuda Cancer Hospital, Guangzhou</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is the safety and efficacy of Rituximab plus NK immunotherapy to
      recurrent B lymphoma.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      By enrolling patients with B lymphoma adapted to enrolled criteria, this study will document
      for the first time the safety and the short and long term efficacy of the combined therapy
      using Rituximab and natural killer (NK) cells.

      The safety will be evaluated by statistics of adverse reactions. The efficacy will be
      evaluated according to local relief degree, progress free survival (PFS) and overall survival
      (OS).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
